## Quick Start

```simple
# Example 1: Check borrows
use compiler_core.borrow_check.{check_borrows}

val result = check_borrows(mir_code)
if result.errors.len() > 0:
    print "Borrow errors found: {result.errors[0]}"
```

```simple
# Example 2: Build borrow graph
use compiler_core.borrow_check.{BorrowGraph}

val graph = BorrowGraph()
graph.add_borrow(var: "x", location: "line 10")
val conflicts = graph.find_conflicts()
```

```simple
# Example 3: Infer lifetimes
use compiler_core.borrow_check.{infer_lifetimes}

val lifetimes = infer_lifetimes(function_body)
print "Lifetimes: {lifetimes.len()}"
```

